Universe != logical computing models

Logical computing date systems (e.g. ISO) are designed to model the physical universe using assumptions and approximations.

Unfortunately, the physical universe does not recognise aproximation based logical models that us weak and fallible humans would wish to superimpose on it.

In knowing the fallibility of computing based logical models versus physical measurements of time, I (together with the rest of the planets human inhabitants) will stick with Gregorgian by convention thank you🤗
